{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, each prompt in the data corresponds to one category of advanced IF capabilities, such as complex instructions within single-turn conversations and multiple instructions throughout multi-turn conversations.",
    "See Section A for a detailed description of the taxonomy.",
    "Moreover, we avoid generating prompts that have ambiguous intentions or overlap with other domains of capabilities (e.g., factuality) to make sure that we concentrate on improving core IF capabilities.",
    "For multi-turn conversations, the annotators first have a conversation with a provided LLM, and then provide instructions in the last turn.",
    "Our prompts are collected in an adversarial way such that they are challenging enough for training -we only keep the prompts that trigger IF failures of the model's response in the final turn."
  ]
}